# Subagent Delegation Rules

Norviq has 4 specialized subagents in .cursor/agents/. Delegate to them in these situations:

## Use parallel review (3 subagents at once)

After any change >50 lines under norviq/, before committing:
- Spawn norviq-correctness-auditor (Task subagent)
- Spawn norviq-security-auditor (Task subagent)
- Spawn norviq-performance-auditor (Task subagent)

Run all THREE in parallel. Wait for all to complete. Merge findings into .reviews/parallel-{sha}.md.

## Use verifier when work is claimed done

When user says "this should work now" or "I'm done with X":
- Spawn norviq-verifier (Task subagent)
- Do not trust the claim - verify.

## Use security auditor alone for security-sensitive changes

Any change to:
- norviq/api/routers/auth.py
- norviq/api/middleware/
- Anything touching JWT verification

## Do NOT use subagents for

- Single-line fixes
- Documentation-only changes
- Test additions
- Config tweaks

Subagents are for analysis. Use them when isolation + parallel execution add value.
